# Climate Closet Design System

## Core Design Philosophy

Climate Closet combines a clean, minimal interface with weather-responsive elements to create a practical, delightful user experience. The design system:

- Prioritizes content and functionality over decorative elements
- Uses a weather-responsive interface that adapts colors and mood to current conditions
- Creates a cohesive experience across all weather states while maintaining brand consistency
- Balances the minimalist black/white approach from the Figma design with modern, subtle color accents
- Presents all critical information in a single view without requiring scrolling
- Uses intentional spacing, typography hierarchy, and color to guide users through the interface

## Color System

### Base Interface Colors
- **Primary Background**: White (#FFFFFF)
- **Secondary Background**: Light gray (#F5F5F5)
- **Primary Text**: Black (#000000)
- **Secondary Text**: Dark gray (#757575)
- **Accent Elements**: Black (#000000) for buttons, icons, and key UI elements
- **Dividers/Borders**: Light gray (#F5F5F5) to medium gray (#E5E5E5)

### Weather-Responsive Accent Palettes
Each weather condition introduces subtle color accents that influence the mood without overwhelming the clean interface. Weather gradients should be applied with transparency/opacity to ensure they're not obtrusive:

- **Sunny**:
  - Accent: Gold/Yellow (#FFDE82)
  - Gradient: Soft yellow to warm orange (#FFDE82 to #FF9B71) with 15-25% opacity
  - Header background tint: Very light yellow (#FFFBF0)

- **Cloudy**:
  - Accent: Steel blue/Gray (#C0C5CE)
  - Gradient: Light to medium gray (#E5E7EB to #D1D5DB) with 15-25% opacity
  - Header background tint: Cool gray (#F7F8FA)

- **Rainy**:
  - Accent: Teal (#64B6AC)
  - Gradient: Light to medium blue (#A6D1E6 to #5591A9) with 15-25% opacity
  - Header background tint: Light blue (#F0F7FF)

- **Snowy**:
  - Accent: Ice blue (#A1C6EA)
  - Gradient: White to very light blue (#FFFFFF to #E1E5F2) with 15-25% opacity
  - Header background tint: Crisp white (#F9FAFF)

- **Night**:
  - Accent: Deep blue (#48466D)
  - Gradient: Dark blue to purple hints (#0D1B2A to #48466D) with 15-25% opacity
  - Header background tint: Very dark blue (#0D1B2A)
  - Text (inverted): White (#FFFFFF)

### Application of Weather-Responsive Design
- The main UI structure remains consistent across all weather conditions
- Weather state influences:
  - Header background gradient/tint
  - Button and accent colors
  - Clothing item borders and highlights
  - Mood and tone of the entire interface

## Typography

### Font Family
- **Primary Font**: Inter (Clean, modern sans-serif)
- **Secondary Font**: Libre Baskerville (For emphasized words in titles, like "Outfit" in "TODAY'S Outfit")

### Typography Scale
- **Header/Title**: 20px, Bold (700), 140% line height
- **Subheader**: 14px, SemiBold (600), 140% line height
- **Body Text**: 11px, Regular (400), 140% line height
- **Small/Caption**: 9px, Regular (400), 140% line height
- **Button Text**: 10px, Bold (700), 140% line height

### Text Styling
- Use italic style for category labels (Top, Bottoms, Outerwear, etc.)
- Maintain consistent casing: Title case for headers, Uppercase for buttons
- Weather labels and day information use Regular (400) weight
- Active/selected items use SemiBold (600) or Bold (700) weight

## Layout & Structure

### Screen Organization
- **Header Section**: Contains greeting, location, date selection
- **Content Section**: Displays outfit recommendations or weather information
- **Action Area**: Contains primary actions (Edit, Save, Share)

### Layout Principles
- Use a consistent grid with 12px base unit for spacing and layout
- Maintain 12px border radius on all rounded elements (buttons, cards)
- Group related information in visually distinct sections
- Use proximity and alignment to create clear visual hierarchy
- Keep primary actions easily accessible within thumb reach

### Card Design
- Use subtle, light gray (#F5F5F5) background for content cards
- Maintain consistent 12px border radius
- Minimize shadows in favor of subtle color differentiation
- Use consistent spacing (12px padding) within cards
- Clothing category labels are placed in a rotated orientation along the edge of each card

### Bento Box Clothing Layout
- Arrange clothing items in a bento box grid layout regardless of screen size
- Each clothing category has its own cell (Top, Bottoms, Outerwear, Shoes, Accessories)
- Allow users to click/tap any clothing item to expand to full-screen view
- Expanded view shows additional details and data about the clothing item
- Include a back arrow or X button to return to the bento box layout

## Component Library

### Buttons
- **Primary Buttons**: Black background (#000000) with white text, pill shape (12px radius)
- **Secondary Buttons**: White background with black border and black text
- **Weather/Outfit Toggle Button**: Pill-shaped button showing temperature and weather icon
- **Size**: Maintain comfortable touch targets (minimum 44x44pt)
- **States**: Include hover, pressed, and disabled states

### Navigation & Selection
- **Date Selection**: Horizontal scrolling dates with clear active state (black background, white text)
- **Category Selection**: Clean, minimal tabs or chips
- **Location Selector**: Input field with location icon
- **Bottom Navigation**: Simplified navigation with icons for:
  - Home/Weather (primary view)
  - Closet/Clothing items
  - Social features
  - Account/Settings

### Weather/Outfit Toggle
- Design as a pill-shaped button rather than text link
- Include current temperature and weather icon (sun, cloud, rain, etc.)
- Positioned near the "TODAY'S Outfit" header
- When clicked, flips the outfit card to display detailed weather information
- Provides immediate context for clothing suggestions

### Weather Icons
- Use distinctive, custom weather icons that match the minimal aesthetic
- Standard size of 24x24px for consistency
- Animate weather icons subtly to indicate current conditions
- Ensure icons are clearly distinguishable at small sizes

## Sponsored Items

- Apply a minimal "sponsored" label to clothing items when needed
- Position label in the lower right corner of the clothing item cell
- Use small, light gray text (9px) with 75% opacity
- Ensure the label doesn't interfere with the visibility of the clothing item
- Example text: "sponsored" in #000000 with 75% opacity

## Rating System

Based on the RatingPage design, the rating system should:

- Display the complete outfit at the top of the rating page
- Provide separate rating sliders for "Upper body" and "Lower body" comfort
- Use a 5-point sliding scale from "Cold" to "Hot"
- Include additional attribute selection options (e.g., "Favorite")
- Use a clean, minimal form design with light gray backgrounds
- Include a prominent "Confirm" button for submitting ratings
- Display all items in the outfit being rated for context

## Animation & Interactions

- Minimize animations throughout the app, with exceptions for:
  - Weather icons (subtle animations to represent weather conditions)
  - Gradient bloom animation when app is first opened
  - Micro-interactions for feedback on user actions
- Keep animations subtle and purposeful
- Ensure animations complete quickly (under 300ms) to maintain responsiveness
- Consider performance implications for older devices

## Accessibility Guidelines

- Maintain WCAG AA contrast ratios (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text)
- Support system text size adjustments
- Ensure all interactive elements have clear focus states
- Design for one-handed use with important actions in thumb zone
- Include alt text for all weather icons and clothing images
- Support system preferences for reduced motion

## Future Design Considerations

- Light/Dark mode support to be implemented in future phases
- Expanded social features and sharing capabilities
- More complex clothing recommendations for trips
- Integration with user's personal clothing inventory
- Additional animations and transitions as the app matures
- AI-powered outfit suggestions based on user preferences and feedback
